00:08:25.890 --> 00:08:28.090
&gt;&gt; Joyce Carol Oates:
Oh that's so nice.

00:08:28.090 --> 00:08:29.390
&gt;&gt; Ron Charles: Yeah.

00:08:29.390 --> 00:08:30.690
What draws you to horror?

00:08:30.690 --> 00:08:32.650
To the Gothic sensibility?

00:08:32.650 --> 00:08:35.020
&gt;&gt; Joyce Carol Oates: Well Gothic
sensibility is almost entirely a

00:08:35.020 --> 00:08:36.760
literary sensibility.

00:08:36.760 --> 00:08:38.060
&gt;&gt; Ron Charles: What
do you mean by that?

00:08:38.060 --> 00:08:39.360
Explain that to us.

00:08:39.360 --> 00:08:40.660
&gt;&gt; Joyce Carol Oates:
There aren't really,

00:08:40.660 --> 00:08:41.960
there were never really
any haunted houses so.

00:08:41.960 --> 00:08:44.260
&gt;&gt; Ron Charles: Oh no Joyce.

00:08:45.270 --> 00:08:46.690
&gt;&gt; Joyce Carol Oates: If
you're writing a novel

00:08:46.690 --> 00:08:50.300
about haunted houses , vampires,
werewolf's and so forth,

00:08:50.300 --> 00:08:54.320
you are not looking
back to an actual,

00:08:54.320 --> 00:08:56.150
