owner or you have the nobleman

00:09:48.630 --> 00:09:58.510
and this could be quote Count
Dracula and so the vampire saga

00:09:58.510 --> 00:10:04.790
or image or epic is
actually a social

00:10:04.790 --> 00:10:09.110
and psychological commentary
on human life.

00:10:09.110 --> 00:10:12.690
So the vampire who's
Dracula is the nobleman,

00:10:12.690 --> 00:10:15.550
he's sucking the blood
of the common people.

00:10:15.550 --> 00:10:22.380 position:56%
He's taking the life, he's taking
the young people, this is just a way

00:10:22.380 --> 00:10:24.730
of talking about politics.

00:10:24.730 --> 00:10:27.980
But it's a Gothic troll.

00:10:27.980 --> 00:10:29.380
Then the werewolf we think

00:10:29.380 --> 00:10:34.630
as probably a dramatization very
literal, you know like fur coming

00:10:34.630 --> 00:10:36.660
out of the face and so forth.

00:10:36.660 --> 00:10:42.030
Of the, what Freud would call the
id in human beings, the unconscious

00:10:42.030 --> 00:10:46.520
that comes out is rapacious
and can be quite evil

00:10:46.520 --> 00:10:49.290
and destructive and
self destructive.

00:10:49.290 --> 00:10:53.520
So the werewolf as a
symbol is a dramatization

00:10:53.520 --> 00:10:56.260
of something that's
psychological and quite normal.

00:10:56.260 --> 00:10:59.290 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Ron Charles: Would you admit that
there's a certain element of comedy

00:10:59.290 --> 00:11:01.290
in some of your Gothic novels?

00:11:01.290 --> 00:11:04.820
&gt;&gt; Joyce Carol Oates: Yes my novels
