had probably tragic lives

00:38:08.540 --> 00:38:13.300
and from broken homes and
discontinuous school and different.

00:38:13.300 --> 00:38:15.670
&gt;&gt; Ron Charles: What an
opportunity for both of you.

00:38:15.670 --> 00:38:17.060
Both groups, you and these men.

00:38:17.060 --> 00:38:18.360
&gt;&gt; Joyce Carol Oates: Yeah and then

00:38:18.360 --> 00:38:22.940
when I edited Prison Noir a
few years later I used a story

00:38:22.940 --> 00:38:24.900
by one of my former students.

00:38:24.900 --> 00:38:26.200
&gt;&gt; Ron Charles: From the prison?

00:38:26.200 --> 00:38:27.500
&gt;&gt; Joyce Carol Oates:
From that prison.

00:38:27.500 --> 00:38:28.800
&gt;&gt; Ron Charles: That's
great, that's great.

00:38:28.800 --> 00:38:30.100
&gt;&gt; Joyce Carol Oates:
Then I looked at stories

00:38:30.100 --> 00:38:32.630
from all the many many
